The paper deals with the problem of gathering in a network modeled as a graph, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC) and graph theory (cs.DS). The presence of Byzantine agents also makes it relevant to the field of fault-tolerant systems (cs.SY). The use of global knowledge with a small binary representation suggests that information theory (cs.IT) may also be relevant. Finally, the focus on designing a deterministic solution with lower complexity suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the field of algorithms (cs.LG).
